SampleDescription.Description: duplicated material resides near the centromere on chromosome 19q, indicating a complex rearrangement rather than a tandem duplication. Chromosome and additional metaphase FISH studies did not reveal evidence for a 19q inversion associated with the duplication. Therefore, the duplication may be the result of an intrachromosomal insertional translocation event. Phenotype: large congenital diaphragmatic hernia, tetralogy of Fallot, dysmorphic features, absent left pulmonary artery
